\f1\b0 \cf2 1. 
\f2 \uc0\u1513 \u1473 \u1490 \u1464 \u1490 \u1464 \u1492 
\f1  (shegagah) \'96 \'93Error\'94 (Unintentional Sin)\
	\'95	Root Meaning: To stumble, wander off course.\
	\'95	Physical Imagery: Like tripping on uneven ground, this term evokes the image of unintentional missteps, as one wandering from a path without awareness. Levitical Context: Represents sins committed accidentally due to ignorance or lack of attention.\
	\'95	Scriptural Reference: Numbers 15:28 \'96 \'93And the priest shall make atonement for the person who sins in error (shegagah).\'94\
\
2. 
\f2 \uc0\u1495 \u1464 \u1496 \u1464 \u1488 
\f1  (chata) \'96 \'93To Miss the Mark\'94 (General Sin)\
	\'95	Root Meaning: To miss a target or fail a shot.\
	\'95	Physical Imagery: The term originates from archery, describing an arrow that fails to hit its mark\'97a deviation from accuracy. Levitical Context: Applies to general moral failures without direct intent to defy.\
	\'95	Scriptural Reference: Leviticus 4:2 \'96 \'93When a person sins unintentionally (chata) against any of the commandments of the Lord\'85\'94\
\
3. 
\f2 \uc0\u1495 \u1463 \u1496 \u1464 \u1468 \u1488 \u1464 \u1492 
\f1  (chatta\'92ah) \'96 \'93Sin Offering\'94 (Ritual Atonement)\
	\'95	Root Meaning: Same as chata, but as a noun.\
	\'95	Physical Imagery: The offering physically represents the missed mark and the need for restitution through sacrifice. Levitical Context: This term shifts from missing the mark to addressing the error through a tangible sacrifice.\
	\'95	Scriptural Reference: Leviticus 4:3 \'96 \'93He must bring to the Lord a young bull as a sin offering (chatta\'92ah).\'94\
\
4. 
\f2 \uc0\u1502 \u1464 \u1506 \u1463 \u1500 
\f1  (ma\'92al) \'96 \'93Unfaithfulness\'94 (Covenant Breach)\
	\'95	Root Meaning: To cover or act covertly, as in deception.\
	\'95	Physical Imagery: Like a cloak concealing wrongdoing, ma\'92al evokes hidden betrayal or a breach of trust behind someone\'92s back.\
	\'95	Levitical Context: Describes faithlessness toward God\'92s covenant, often involving desecration of holy things.\
	\'95	Scriptural Reference: Leviticus 5:15 \'96 \'93If a person commits a breach of faith (ma\'92al) and sins unintentionally in regard to the holy things of the Lord\'85\'94\
\
5. 
\f2 \uc0\u1488 \u1464 \u1513 \u1464 \u1473 \u1501 
\f1  (asham) \'96 \'93Guilt\'94 or \'93Guilt Offering\'94\
	\'95	Root Meaning: To feel weight or burdened.\
	\'95	Physical Imagery: This term captures the sensation of carrying a heavy load, emphasizing guilt as a tangible burden pressing on the soul.\
	\'95	Levitical Context: Describes guilt awareness requiring both sacrifice and restitution.\
	\'95	Scriptural Reference: Leviticus 5:6 \'96 \'93He shall bring his guilt offering (asham) to the Lord for his sin which he has committed.\'94\
\
6. 
\f2 \uc0\u1506 \u1464 \u1493 \u1465 \u1503 
\f1  (avon) \'96 \'93Iniquity\'94 (Moral Distortion)\
	\'95	Root Meaning: To bend, twist, or distort something straight.\
	\'95	Physical Imagery: Imagine a warped plank or a crooked path\'97this word emphasizes moral perversion and a twisting of divine law from its original intent.\
	\'95	Levitical Context: Often paired with unconfessed sin, resulting in corrupted character and moral decay.\
	\'95	Scriptural Reference: Leviticus 16:21 \'96 \'93Confess over the goat all the iniquities (avon) of the Israelites.\'94\
\
7. 
\f2 \uc0\u1488 \u1464 \u1493 \u1462 \u1503 
\f1  (aven) \'96 \'93Vanity\'94 or \'93Idolatry\'94 (Moral Emptiness)\
	\'95	Root Meaning: To pant, exert effort in vain.\
	\'95	Physical Imagery: The word describes chasing after wind, expending energy without result, emphasizing the emptiness of idolatry and false pursuits.\
	\'95	Levitical Context: Describes vain offerings and idolatry, focusing on futility.\
	\'95	Scriptural Reference: Isaiah 1:13 \'96 \'93Bring no more vain (aven) offerings; incense is an abomination to me.\'94\
\
8. 
\f2 \uc0\u1512 \u1462 \u1513 \u1463 \u1473 \u1506 
\f1  (resha) \'96 \'93Wickedness\'94 (Criminal Sin)\
	\'95	Root Meaning: To be loud, turbulent, agitated.\
	\'95	Physical Imagery: Think of a storming sea\'97resha conveys the disturbance of moral order, violence or agitated wrongdoing.\
	\'95	Levitical Context: Describes a state of rebellion resulting in active harm against God\'92s commands and society.\
	\'95	Scriptural Reference: Psalm 45:7 \'96 \'93You love righteousness and hate wickedness (resha).\'94\
\
9. 
\f2 \uc0\u1508 \u1462 \u1468 \u1513 \u1463 \u1473 \u1506 
\f1  (pesha) \'96 \'93Transgression\'94 (Defiant Rebellion)\
	\'95	Root Meaning: To break away, breach, or rebel.\
	\'95	Physical Imagery: Picture breaking through a wall or tearing a boundary, emphasizing open defiance against God\'92s authority.\
	\'95	Levitical Context: Describes open covenant rebellion, often resulting in divine judgment.\
	\'95	Scriptural Reference: Leviticus 26:40 \'96 \'93They will confess their iniquity and the iniquity of their fathers\'85and their rebellion (pesha).\'94\
