The Physicality of Sin: The biblical language for sin is profoundly rooted in physical experiences, grounding spiritual realities in bodily metaphors. The progression from stumbling (shegagah) to rebellion (pesha) reflects a moral descent from unintentional error to deliberate defiance. Each stage reflects increasing relational damage\'97from self-inflicted error to open rebellion against God\'92s covenant.}